This project follows Clean Architecture.

Layers:

1. Presentation Layer
   - API Controllers
   - DTOs
   - Request/Response models

2. Application Layer
   - Use Cases
   - Application Services
   - Interfaces

3. Domain Layer
   - Entities
   - Value Objects
   - Domain Services
   - Domain Events

4. Infrastructure Layer
   - Database access
   - External APIs
   - File storage
   - Email services

Rules:

1. Domain layer must not depend on any other layer.

2. Application layer may depend only on domain.

3. Infrastructure depends on all layers.

4. Controllers must never access repositories directly.

5. Controllers must call use cases.

6. Use cases contain business logic.

7. Repositories must be interfaces in Application layer.

8. Repository implementations must exist in Infrastructure.

9. DTOs must not leak domain entities.

10. Never expose database models to the API.
